<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="473" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1086,1833]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1410,1436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from the other members of the genus found within the same area by the position and number of spicules in the girdle tufts and the valve sculpturing. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Rios" authorityYear="2006" box="[913,1234,1446,1472]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Tonicellidae" genus="Lepidochitona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salvadorensis">
<emphasis box="[913,1234,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Lepidochitona salvadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears tufts of 2–6 hyaline spicules located near the girdle base and microgranular sculpturing appearing without sculpture, in contrast with the sympatric 
<taxonomicName box="[363,461,1518,1545]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Tonicellidae" genus="Lepidochitona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beanii">
<emphasis box="[363,379,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[391,461,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">beanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that exhibits tufts of 3–4 spicules located at the valve sutures and with somewhat raised lateral areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1086,1833]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia-Rios, C. I." box="[199,417,1590,1617]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="206 - 214" refId="ref20997" refString="Garcia-Rios, C. I. (2006) A new species of Lepidochitona (Mollusca; Polyplacohora) from El Salvador. The Veliger, 48 (3), 206 - 214." type="journal article" year="2006">García-Ríos (2006)</bibRefCitation>
reported that the maximum body size observed for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Rios" authorityYear="2006" box="[1004,1188,1590,1617]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Tonicellidae" genus="Lepidochitona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salvadorensis">
<emphasis box="[1004,1020,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1035,1188,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">salvadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<quantity box="[1227,1314,1590,1617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" unit="mm" value="9.8">9.8 mm</quantity>
(specimen from Los Cobanos, 
<collectingRegion box="[377,488,1626,1653]" country="El Salvador" name="La Union" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">La Unión</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[500,638,1626,1653]" name="El Salvador" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">El Salvador</collectingCountry>
). Our largest specimen (
<quantity box="[913,1015,1626,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1199999999999999" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" unit="mm" value="11.2">11.2 mm</quantity>
of body length) is from Parque de la Reina, Acapulco (e.g., UAGRO 0040). This species was first recorded from southern Mexican waters at Estacahuite, Puerto Ángel, Oaxaca (
<bibRefCitation author="Reyes-Gomez, A. &amp; Barrientos-Lujan, N. A. &amp; Medina-Bautista, J. &amp; Ramirez-Luna, S." box="[418,712,1698,1725]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="111 - 125" refId="ref22764" refString="Reyes-Gomez, A., Barrientos-Lujan, N. A., Medina-Bautista, J. &amp; Ramirez-Luna, S. (2010) Chitons from the coralline area of Oaxaca, Mexico (Polyplacophora). Bollettino Malacologico, 46, 111 - 125." type="journal article" year="2010">
Reyes-Gómez 
<emphasis box="[587,639,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
) and at Bahía Navachiste, Sinaloa, Jalisco and Nayarit (ReyesGómez 2016). These reports suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Rios" authorityYear="2006" box="[636,822,1734,1761]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Tonicellidae" genus="Lepidochitona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salvadorensis">
<emphasis box="[636,652,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[669,822,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">salvadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distributed throughout the Mexican Tropical Pacific, however, more exploration is needed in the central Mexican Pacific (Michoacán, Colima) and elsewhere before it is considered to have a continuous distribution range between Guerrero and 
<collectingCountry box="[1105,1239,1806,1832]" name="El Salvador" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">El Salvador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
